see http://jubat.us/

usage:
------
0. install git, gcc, ruby, libtool, automake and autoconf 
1. add jubatus.profile to your .xshrc or source jubatus.profile
2. run install.sh

if you want to use python client,

3. install python-dev
4. run install_python.sh

install.sh -dip
 d : only download
 i : only install
 p : install path
 D : install develop branch

example:
---------

# ./install.sh -i -p /usr/local/

if you want to install jubatus another directory,
fix $PREFIX and jubatus.profile.
